        "Name": "Rifleman",
        "Details": "A recently developed House Marik model, the RFL-3M trades out both of the arm mounted Large Lasers for additional AC/5s in each arm.  While this reduces the damage output for the tradeoff of extending the overall damage range slightly.  The engine was also reduced, making the RFL-3M even slower and a half ton of armor was removed.  The real benefit is the decreased heat output, allowing the 3M to maintain a steady stream of long range fire.  Unfortunately, the 'Mech is still limited to a single ton of ammo, so it is not an ideal long term deployment choice.<br><br>S-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that substantially improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
